<title>
Inside Air Temperature Sensor Inspection
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Blow hot air to inside air temperature sensor (1), and measure resistance by using ohmmeter (2).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check that the resistance decreases as temperature rises as shown.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If check result is not as specified, replace inside air temperature sensor.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<spec>
<title>
Inside air temperature sensor specification
</title>
<ptxt>
0 °C (32 °F): 5.22 – 5.78 Ω
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
25 °C (77 °F): 1.61 – 1.79 Ω
</ptxt>
</spec>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A723015.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "75.189mm" ver = "02" gw = "183" gh = "197"/>
</figure>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A723032.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "46.394mm" ver = "01" gw = "148" gh = "115"/>
</figure>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
